= 4 JUSTIFICATION

No automated tools or annotated datasets exist for analyzing Robot Sumo matches from video. All analysis relies on human observation, which is subjective, non-scalable, and produces no permanent record. Historical competition knowledge is lost with each generation of competitors, and teams design new robots based on intuition without access to real combat data.

In the computer vision literature, the domain of scenarios with extreme speed, ultra-short duration, and small visually similar objects remains underexplored. This work fills that gap by proposing the first automated pipeline for detection, tracking, and performance metric extraction in Robot Sumo, accompanied by the first public annotated dataset representative of the current competitive category.
